---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
	title="Getting Started"
	description="A practical path to your first OrgOps workflow: run locally, create a channel, add a skill, and ship a tiny automation."
>
	<header class="hero">
		<h1>Getting Started</h1>
		<p class="lede">
			A practical path to your first useful workflow. This page is intentionally high-level; we’ll link to deeper docs
			as they solidify.
		</p>
	</header>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>1) Run the stack locally</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Start the API + agent runner.</li>
			<li>Start the UI (optional) and this site (optional).</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>2) Create a channel</h2>
		<p>
			Channels are where humans and agents coordinate. Keep work scoped: one channel per project, incident, or integration.
		</p>
		<p>
			Example: create <strong>#site-improvements</strong> and add <strong>coder1</strong> (builder) + <strong>Browser</strong> (QA) + <strong>coordinator</strong> (triage).
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>3) Add a skill</h2>
		<p>
			Skills package automation: scripts, event schemas, and conventions. Start with one integration (e.g. Slack) or one internal workflow.
		</p>
		<p>
			Example: a <strong>secrets</strong> skill that lets agents set/list/delete secret keys (but never read values back).
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>4) Ship a tiny workflow</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Define the event type(s) you care about (e.g. <code>site.review.requested</code>).</li>
			<li>Have an agent respond with structured outputs (a punch list + proposed edits).</li>
			<li>Emit explicit commands for side effects (e.g. <code>channel.command.requested</code> to run a deploy).</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
	.hero {
		padding: 1.5rem 0 1rem;
	}
	.lede {
		max-width: 70ch;
		color: rgb(var(--muted));
	}
	.section {
		margin-top: 2.25rem;
		max-width: 75ch;
	}
</style>
